26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_i2c_aux.c,v 1.3 2018/08/27 07:38:42 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "aux.h"
30#include "pad.h"
31
32static int
33nvkm_i2c_aux_i2c_xfer(struct i2c_adapter *adap, struct i2c_msg *msgs, int num)
34{
35 struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux = container_of(adap, typeof(*aux), i2c);
36 struct i2c_msg *msg = msgs;
37 int ret, mcnt = num;
38
39 ret = nvkm_i2c_aux_acquire(aux);
40 if (ret)
41 return ret;
42
43 while (mcnt--) {
44 u8 remaining = msg->len;
45 u8 *ptr = msg->buf;
46
47 while (remaining) {
48 u8 cnt = (remaining > 16) ? 16 : remaining;
49 u8 cmd;
50
51 if (msg->flags & I2C_M_RD)
52 cmd = 1;
53 else
54 cmd = 0;
55
56 if (mcnt || remaining > 16)
57 cmd |= 4; /* MOT */
58
59 ret = aux->func->xfer(aux, true, cmd, msg->addr, ptr, cnt);
60 if (ret < 0) {
61 nvkm_i2c_aux_release(aux);
62 return ret;
63 }
64
65 ptr += cnt;
66 remaining -= cnt;
67 }
68
69 msg++;
70 }
71
72 nvkm_i2c_aux_release(aux);
73 return num;
74}
75
76static u32
77nvkm_i2c_aux_i2c_func(struct i2c_adapter *adap)
78{
79 return I2C_FUNC_I2C | I2C_FUNC_SMBUS_EMUL;
80}
81
82const struct i2c_algorithm
83nvkm_i2c_aux_i2c_algo = {
84 .master_xfer = nvkm_i2c_aux_i2c_xfer,
85 .functionality = nvkm_i2c_aux_i2c_func
86};
87
88void
89nvkm_i2c_aux_monitor(struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux, bool monitor)
90{
91 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad = aux->pad;
92 AUX_TRACE(aux, "monitor: %s", monitor ? "yes" : "no");
93 if (monitor)
94 nvkm_i2c_pad_mode(pad, NVKM_I2C_PAD_AUX);
95 else
96 nvkm_i2c_pad_mode(pad, NVKM_I2C_PAD_OFF);
97}
98
99void
100nvkm_i2c_aux_release(struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux)
101{
102 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad = aux->pad;
103 AUX_TRACE(aux, "release");
104 nvkm_i2c_pad_release(pad);
105 mutex_unlock(&aux->mutex);
106}
107
108int
109nvkm_i2c_aux_acquire(struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux)
110{
111 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad = aux->pad;
112 int ret;
113 AUX_TRACE(aux, "acquire");
114 mutex_lock(&aux->mutex);
115 ret = nvkm_i2c_pad_acquire(pad, NVKM_I2C_PAD_AUX);
116 if (ret)
117 mutex_unlock(&aux->mutex);
118 return ret;
119}
120
121int
122nvkm_i2c_aux_xfer(struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux, bool retry, u8 type,
123 u32 addr, u8 *data, u8 size)
124{
125 return aux->func->xfer(aux, retry, type, addr, data, size);
126}
127
128int
129nvkm_i2c_aux_lnk_ctl(struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux, int nr, int bw, bool ef)
130{
131 if (aux->func->lnk_ctl)
132 return aux->func->lnk_ctl(aux, nr, bw, ef);
133 return -ENODEV;
134}
135
136void
137nvkm_i2c_aux_del(struct nvkm_i2c_aux **paux)
138{
139 struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux = *paux;
140 if (aux && !WARN_ON(!aux->func)) {
141 AUX_TRACE(aux, "dtor");
142 list_del(&aux->head);
143 i2c_del_adapter(&aux->i2c);
144#ifdef __NetBSD__
145 linux_mutex_destroy(&aux->mutex);
146#else
147 mutex_destroy(&aux->mutex);
148#endif
149 kfree(*paux);
150 *paux = NULL;
151 }
152}
153
154int
155nvkm_i2c_aux_ctor(const struct nvkm_i2c_aux_func *func,
156 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad, int id,
157 struct nvkm_i2c_aux *aux)
158{
159 struct nvkm_device *device = pad->i2c->subdev.device;
160
161 aux->func = func;
162 aux->pad = pad;
163 aux->id = id;
164#ifdef __NetBSD__
165 linux_mutex_init(&aux->mutex);
166#else
167 mutex_init(&aux->mutex);
168#endif
169 list_add_tail(&aux->head, &pad->i2c->aux);
170 AUX_TRACE(aux, "ctor");
171
172 snprintf(aux->i2c.name, sizeof(aux->i2c.name), "nvkm-%s-aux-%04x",
173 dev_name(device->dev), id);
174 aux->i2c.owner = THIS_MODULE;
175 aux->i2c.dev.parent = device->dev;
176 aux->i2c.algo = &nvkm_i2c_aux_i2c_algo;
177 return i2c_add_adapter(&aux->i2c);
178}
179
180int
181nvkm_i2c_aux_new_(const struct nvkm_i2c_aux_func *func,
182 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad, int id,
183 struct nvkm_i2c_aux **paux)
184{
185 if (!(*paux = kzalloc(sizeof(**paux), GFP_KERNEL)))
186 return -ENOMEM;
187 return nvkm_i2c_aux_ctor(func, pad, id, *paux);
188}
